12:08.343 --> 12:09.352
Fifteen seconds.

12:09.352 --> 12:10.201
Oh.

12:10.201 --> 12:11.830
What is wrong with your brother today?

12:11.830 --> 12:12.624
Oh, ignore him.

12:12.624 --> 12:14.751
You know, 
human nature never ceases to amaze me. 

12:14.751 --> 12:18.762
How otherwise rational people can be turned into 
babbling ninnies by their hormones.

12:18.762 --> 12:30.904
OH MY GOD! IT'S GARY! OH MY GOD! IT'S HIM, IT'S HIM!

12:30.904 --> 12:32.363
Well, we're back.

12:32.363 --> 12:35.605
You'll all be glad to know that 
Cupid's arrow has hit its mark.

12:35.605 --> 12:41.518
Gary has just arrived in the hallway, 
and has a big bouquet of flowers for Roz.

12:41.518 --> 12:44.312
You know, the truth is, I'm really quite delighted 
with the way things have turned out today.

12:44.312 --> 12:48.626
It inspires me to take a little leap of my own.

12:48.626 --> 12:54.728
As many of you know, this evening, for the third year 
in a row I will be appearing on the P.B.S. pledge drive...

12:54.728 --> 12:57.079
You know, I was getting a little nervous, 
the way you were describing me on the air.

12:57.079 --> 12:58.650
Why?

12:58.650 --> 13:00.434
Well, my wife listens to the show.

13:00.434 --> 13:01.575
You're married?

13:01.575 --> 13:06.825
Yeah, but it's okay.  
I still want to go out with you.

13:06.825 --> 13:14.891
So, instead of Buttons and Bows, I have chosen to sing 
a very challenging aria from Verdi's Rigoletto -

13:14.891 --> 13:18.298
something I have never attempted outside the shower.

13:18.298 --> 13:34.144
I certainly hope 
my little gamble turns out as well as Roz's has.

13:34.144 --> 13:46.314
Or even better.

13:46.314 --> 13:47.872
Oh, God!

13:47.872 --> 13:53.218
Well, perhaps they'll pledge to get 
you to stop singing.

13:53.218 --> 13:55.894
Oh, and by the way, thanks so much for 
the cold shower tip.

13:55.894 --> 13:56.720
Did it work?

13:56.720 --> 14:02.905
No, it did not.  It's clearly an old wives tail, 
because I'm still thinking of my old wife's tail.

14:02.905 --> 14:08.513
Yes, well I suppose it stood to reason being showered 
with coldness would only bring Maris more to mind.

14:08.513 --> 14:10.560
Keep making remarks like that, 
I won't help you rehearse.

14:10.560 --> 14:11.619
Oh, I'm sorry, Niles.

14:11.619 --> 14:13.280
It's just that I'm awfully nervous.

14:13.280 --> 14:21.763
You know, as much as I admire your willingness to take a leap, 
I did warn you that you were getting into a dangerous aria.?

14:21.763 --> 14:24.262
Oh God, I'm using humor to mask sexual frustration.

14:24.262 --> 14:25.588
It's high school all over again.

14:25.588 --> 14:30.755
Look Niles, I know it's difficult, but Maris has got to learn 
that you're not just someone who can be ordered to perform at will.

14:30.755 --> 14:39.954
Now sit, play!

14:39.954 --> 14:43.914
Next time it looks like I’m going to follow a piece 
of your advice, shoot me in the head first!

14:43.914 --> 14:46.024
Dad!  Why aren't you in Montana?

14:46.024 --> 14:49.934
Fifteen minutes out, a flock of Canadian geese flew 
into one of our engines.

14:49.934 --> 14:52.617
They were the lucky ones!

14:52.617 --> 14:54.707
Next thing you know, 
we're falling five thousand feet.

14:54.707 --> 14:59.665
Smokehouse almonds are flying everywhere, 
people arescreaming and hugging each other.

14:59.665 --> 15:04.756
The guy in the next seat grabbed hold of my hand, 
and you know what? I didn't pull it away!

15:04.756 --> 15:06.153
Then our pilot comes out.

15:06.153 --> 15:10.944
Our landing gear's out, we're gonna have to do 
an emergency belly landing in six feet of foam!

15:10.944 --> 15:15.560
So, five hellish minutes later, 
we're bouncing across the runway.

15:15.560 --> 15:19.304
Then the stewardess comes out and says we're gonna 
have to go down the emergency slide.

15:19.304 --> 15:22.561
So down I go, headfirst into this sea of foam.

15:22.561 --> 15:31.051
Last thing I remember, this fat lady rom across the aisle comes 
barreling down the chute after me like a polyester avalanche!

15:31.051 --> 15:33.499
My God, Dad, I am so sorry.

15:33.499 --> 15:36.483
So-so, these stewardesses, 
were they also covered with foam?

15:36.483 --> 15:50.204
Will you stop it!  Dad, if you'd like to talk about it, 
we're both here for you.

15:50.204 --> 15:55.169
Boy, I tell you, times like this, you just..  
all you can think of is your loved ones,

15:55.169 --> 15:58.668
and how you wish you'd spent more time with them.

15:58.668 --> 16:02.348
Eddie!

16:02.348 --> 16:03.534
Well, let's get back to work.

16:03.534 --> 16:04.630
Mmm-hmm.

16:04.630 --> 16:07.054
I need something to take my mind off the fact 
that at this very moment,

16:07.054 --> 16:15.046
Maris is slipping out of her frilly under-things 
and into a non-fat milk bath.

16:15.046 --> 16:16.421
Is something wrong?

16:16.421 --> 16:20.135
Yes, something’s wrong.  Things turned out so badly for 
Roz and Dad today,

16:20.135 --> 16:24.352
I'm just wondering if my little leap is ill-advised.

16:24.352 --> 16:25.165
Oh, now...

16:25.165 --> 16:27.752
Maybe this aria thing won't turn out so well, 
either.

16:27.752 --> 16:30.078
Just because theirs went wrong 
doesn't mean yours will, too.

16:30.078 --> 16:30.726
Yeah...

16:30.726 --> 16:31.749
They're two isolated incidents.

16:31.749 --> 16:51.512
All right.

16:51.512 --> 16:58.880
Oh, will these infernal temptations never end?!

16:58.880 --> 17:05.327
Oh, tell me the truth.  
Is it as bad as I think it is?

17:05.327 --> 17:10.880
How... bad do you think it is?

17:10.880 --> 17:16.342
Take a leap!  Mr.Maurice hair-designer!  
Trust me!

17:16.342 --> 17:22.286
Children pointing!  Your fault!

17:22.286 --> 17:25.512
Okay, that's it.  I can't take it anymore, 
I'm leaving.

17:25.512 --> 17:27.621
No, Niles!  You can't leave me now, 
I need you more now than ever.

17:27.621 --> 17:32.440
Oh, give it up.  No one who's followed your little 
Take a leap philosophy has ended up even remotely better.

17:32.440 --> 17:37.470
I don't care what you're saying, 
I'm going to Maris.

17:37.470 --> 17:40.072
You will rue the day!

17:40.072 --> 17:59.877
I don't care!  Niles gotta have it!

17:59.877 --> 18:00.793
Oh, Pete.

18:00.793 --> 18:04.655
Hi, Doc.  
I hear you're doing something new this year. Whoa!

18:04.655 --> 18:06.357
What, is it too hard for you?

18:06.357 --> 18:07.760
Me?  No, I'm-I'm worried about you.

